{"title_page": "Anaita Shroff Adajania", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian fashion stylist, costume designer and actress}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox fashion designer\n|image= Anaita Shroff Adajania.JPG\n|caption=\n|name= Anaita Shroff Adajania\n|nationality= Indian\n|birth_date=  {{birth based on age as of date |40|2013|01|06}}<ref name=mum/>\n|birth_place= [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]]\n|death_date=\n|death_place= \n|death_cause=\n|resting_place= \n|education=\n|label_name=\n|years_active=1995- present \n|occupation    = Fashion stylist, costume designer<br>Fashion Director [[Vogue India]]\n|spouse= [[Homi Adajania]] (2002- present)\n|significant_design=\n|relatives=\n|website= \n|}}\n'''Anaita Shroff Adajania''' is an [[India]]n [[fashion stylist]], [[costume designer]] and actress. She is the Fashion Director for ''[[Vogue India]]'' magazine.\n\n==Early life==\nAdajania is a [[Parsis|Parsi]].<ref name=\"Rediff\"/>\n\n==Career==\nShe started her career as assistant fashion editor with ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'' magazine, upon its Indian launch in 1996.<ref>\n{{cite web| title = 5 steps to being a stylist: Anaita Shroff |publisher=Hindustan Times| url = http://www.hindustantimes.com/news-feed/fashionguru/5-steps-to-being-a-stylist-anaita-shroff/article1-573612.aspx |date=17 July 2010| accessdate = 23 December 2013 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100718094605/http://www.hindustantimes.com/news-feed/fashionguru/5-steps-to-being-a-stylist-anaita-shroff/article1-573612.aspx | archive-date=18 July 2010 | url-status=dead }}</ref> Subsequently, she worked with ''[[L'Officiel]] India'', before becoming the fashion director at ''Vogue India''.<ref name=mum>{{cite web|title=Q&A With Vogue Fashion Director Anaita Shroff Adajania |publisher=Mumbai Boss |url=http://mumbaiboss.com/2013/01/06/in-conversation-with-vogue-fashion-director-anaita-shroff-adajania/ |date=6 January 2013 |accessdate=23 December 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224101451/http://mumbaiboss.com/2013/01/06/in-conversation-with-vogue-fashion-director-anaita-shroff-adajania/ |archivedate=24 December 2013 | url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title = Fashion Director Anaita Shroff Adajania |publisher= www.vogue.in | url = http://www.vogue.in/content/fashion-guide-muted-colours|date=12 August 2010| accessdate = 23 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe owner of the Style Cell company, Adajania has been noted for her design work on several [[Bollywood]] films including ''[[Dhoom 2]]'', ''[[Being Cyrus]]'', ''[[Everybody Says I'm Fine!]]'', ''[[Love Aaj Kal]]'' and ''[[Cocktail (2012 film)|Cocktail]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Anaita Shroff - The stylist for Dhoom 2 |url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/features/dhoom2-010107.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120715071354/http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/features/dhoom2-010107.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=15 July 2012 }}</ref> She has notably styled all three films in the ''[[Dhoom (film series)|Dhoom series]]'', starting with ''[[Dhoom]]'' (2004) where she worked with [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]] and [[Esha Deol]]'s look, followed by ''[[Dhoom 2]]'' (2006) where in she worked with [[Aishwarya Rai Bachchan]], [[Hrithik Roshan]] and [[Bipasha Basu]], then in 2013 edition of the franchise ''[[Dhoom 3]]'', she styled [[Katrina Kaif]].<ref>{{cite web| title = Dhoom 3: Body of work|publisher=Livemint| url = http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/TgqxUdKWBm8re0DuX1BqOM/Dhoom-3-Body-of-work.html|date=20 December 2013| accessdate = 23 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nHer designs have also been featured in magazines including [[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]], [[L'Officiel]], [[Elle (magazine)|Elle]] and [[Rolling Stone]].<ref name=\"Rediff\">{{cite web|title=Making Hrithik, Ash look super hot |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/nov/28asa.htm|publisher=Rediff.com, movies|date=28 November 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Anaita Shroff Adajania|url=http://chatinterviews.indiatimes.com/articleshow/883404.cms|date=12 October 2004|publisher=Indiatimes}}</ref> Shroff also currently styles actress [[Deepika Padukone]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Blaggan|first1=Ishita|title=NDTV Exclusive: Finding Fanny Designer Anaita Shroff on Dressing Dimple and the Sixth Oddball|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/ndtv-exclusive-finding-fanny-designer-anaita-shroff-on-dressing-dimple-and-the-sixth-oddball-662997|accessdate=9 January 2016|publisher=NDTV|date=12 September 2014}}</ref> exclusively for all of her events.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hrithik and Deepika have Anaita to thank|url=http://www.emirates247.com/entertainment/hrithik-and-deepika-have-anaita-to-thank-2013-02-18-1.495334|publisher=Emirates247.com|date=18 February 2013}}</ref>\n\nApart from this, she has acted in walk-on roles in films, like ''[[Dilwale Dulhaniya Le Jayenge]]'' (1995), wherein she played Sheena, Simran's ([[Kajol]]) friend in London whom Raj ([[Shah Rukh Khan]]) flirts with at the start of the European trip.  In ''[[Kal Ho Naa Ho]]'' (2003), she played Gita, Rohit's ([[Saif Ali Khan]]) friend. <ref>[https://trendykendy.com/10-most-fashionable-men-in-bollywood/ She also started her new talk show called 'Feet up with stars' on Voot.</ref>]\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 1995||''[[Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge]]''||Sheena (Simran's friend)|| walk on role\n|-\n| 2001||''[[Everybody Says I'm Fine!]]''|| Stylist ||\n|-\n|2003||[[Kal Ho Na Ho]]|| Gita (Rohit's friend)|| walk on role\n|-\n|2004||''[[Dhoom]]''||stylist ||\n|-\n|2006||''[[Being Cyrus]]''||stylist ||\n|-\n| 2006||''[[Hope and a Little Sugar]]''|| ||\n|-\n|2006|| ''[[Kabhi Alvida Naa Kehna]]''||stylist ||\n|-\n|2006||''[[Dhoom 2]]''||stylist ||\n|-\n|2008||''[[Krazzy 4]]''|| ||\n|-\n| 2008 ||''[[Bhoothnath]]''|| ||\n|-\n|2009 ||''[[Love Aaj Kal]]''|| stylist ||\n|-\n|2011||''[[Ra.One]]''|| ||\n|-\n|2011||''[[Players (2012 film)|Players]]''|| ||\n|-\n|2012||''[[Cocktail]]''||stylist ||\n|-\n|2013||''[[Race 2]]''||stylist ||\n|-\n| 2013 ||''[[Dhoom 3]]''|| stylist ||\n|-\n|2014||''[[Lekar Hum Deewana Dil]]''|| ||\n|-\n|2014||''[[Finding Fanny Fernandes]]''||stylist ||\n|-\n|2014||''[[Bang Bang (2014 film)|Bang Bang]]''|| ||\n|-\n|2016||''[[Dear Zindagi]]''|| ||\n|}\n\n==Personal life==\n[[File:Anaita Shroff Adajania, Homi Adajania at India's 50 Best Dressed Men, 2012 (18).jpg|thumb|150px| With husband [[Homi Adajania]], 2012.]]\nShe married Indian film director and screenwriter [[Homi Adajania]] in 2002 who directed ''[[Being Cyrus]]'' (2006) and ''[[Cocktail (2012 film)|Cocktail]]'' (2012). The couple has two boys, Zreh and Zane and she is the sister of [[Scherezade Shroff]].<ref>{{cite web | title = Ten things you should know about Cocktail's director, Homi Adajania |publisher= Firstpost| url = http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/ten-things-you-should-know-about-cocktails-director-homi-adajania-374770.html|date=11 July 2012|accessdate = 23 December 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|- bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\" align=\"center\"\n|-\n! Year || Award Giving Body || Category || Work || Result || Ref\n|-\n| 2007 || [[8th IIFA Awards]] || [[IIFA Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]] ||  ''[[Dhoom 2]]'' || {{won}} || <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altfg.com/film/indian-film-academy-awards-2007/|title=Indian Academy Film Awards: Aamir Khan Bollywood Political Musical + Hrithik Roshan & Rani Mukherji Among Winners|publisher=}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2010 || [[11th IIFA Awards]] || Best Costume Design<br>(shared with [[Dolly Ahluwalia]]) || ''[[Love Aaj Kal]]'' || {{won}} || <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.iifa.com/iifa-years/iifa-years-2010/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=20 March 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160315135944/http://www.iifa.com/iifa-years/iifa-years-2010/ |archive-date=15 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==References